Situated in the central south precinct of Willawong, approximately 16 kilometres from the Brisbane CBD and within close proximity to the Logan Motorway, Centenary Motorway, Ipswich and Beaudesert Roads. The combination of which makes up the major arterial road network of this southside industrial precinct. 

Key Benefits Includes: 
+ 2,260sqm distribution facility 
+ Multiple electric container height roller doors
+ ESFR sprinklers 
+ 13m internal height
+ Functional & heavy duty hardstand areas for loading and unloading 
+ Small office amenity 

Major Motorways: 

+ 4km* to Beaudesert Road 
+ 6km* to Ipswich Motorway
+ 7km* to Logan & Centenaray Motorways 
+ 8.8km& to Gateway Motorway 

For further information please contact exclusive agent Jack Hardy from CBRE.

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Frontage to Bowhill and Sherbrooke Roads

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Be the first to capitalise on this never before offered opportunity in the Brisbane southern industrial market.  The property is 16kms south of the Brisbane CBD with frontage to Bowhill and Sherbrooke Roads, Willawong.

The property at 182 Bowhill Road, Willawong is 21.25 ha and can provide multiple occupiers a strategic “last mile” facility in the Brisbane market and also excellent linkages to all major arterial networks.

Australia’s major capital cities are experiencing significant demand for industrial property, and with the recent Covid restrictions there has been a big surge in online shopping and the need for quick delivery times. 

There are development plans in place for multiple buildings ranging in size from 10,000sqm up to 80,000sqm.  

The site is located approximately 16 kms south of the Brisbane CBD and just south of the Archerfield Airport. This location is at the northern end of the southside’s “Golden Triangle” comprising Ipswich Road, Beaudesert and the Logan Motorway.
This location allows quick access to:

• The CBD and surrounding population

• Qld Rail Marshalling Yards in Acacia Ridge

• Beaudesert Road, which runs south to provide connectivity to the Logan Motorway

• The Logan Motorway is the main connector road in the southern corridor providing a link from the Pacific Motorway to the east across the southern market west to Wacol. It also connects to the Gateway Motorway allowing access to the Brisbane Port and Brisbane Airport.

For further information or to arrange an inspection please contact Exclusive Agent Peter Turnbull

150 Dalmeny Street is strategically located in the central south industrial precinct of Willawong, approximately 15km from the Brisbane CBD. The property connects to Paradise Road which has direct access to the Logan Motorway and is within close proximity to Centenary Motorway, Ipswich & Beaudesert Road. 

Key features include: 
-	Tenancy areas ranging from 2,308sqm* to 2,954sqm* 
-	Clearspan tilt panel warehouse with up to 8.6m internal height 
-	Corporate office accommodation with male and female amenity 
-	Multiple roller door access points with undercover loading 
-	Excellent concrete hardstand for truck turning and container set down
-	Available Q4 2021 

For further information or to arrange an inspection, please contact Jack Hardy from CBRE

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: A-GRADE WAREHOUSING WITH SIGNIFICANT CONCRETE HARDSTAND

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE is pleased to exclusively offer 3/30 Gardens Drive, Willawong to the market for lease. Located in the Willawong Industrial Estate, approximately 14km south of the Brisbane CBD, has direct access to Paradise Road and is in close proximity to SEQ’s major arterial links.

+ 600sqm* modern facility
+ 500sqm* high bay, clear span warehouse
+ 100sqm* first floor office and storage area
+ Three phase power points throughout
+ Container storage & set down area
+ 7 allocated on site car parks
*Approx. 

For more information or to arrange an inspection please contact the Exclusive CBRE agent.
